## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="482a3-102">Um <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding> associa um <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseGesture> com um <xref:System.Windows.Input.ICommand> implementação.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="482a3-102">A <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding> associates a <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseGesture> with an <xref:System.Windows.Input.ICommand> implementation.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="482a3-103"><xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> é a implementação principal do <xref:System.Windows.Input.ICommand> a interface para o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winclient](~/includes/tla2sharptla-winclient-md.md)] ordenar o sistema.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="482a3-103"><xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> is the primary implementation of the <xref:System.Windows.Input.ICommand> interface for the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winclient](~/includes/tla2sharptla-winclient-md.md)] commanding system.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="482a3-104">Em geral, quando o <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseGesture> é executado, o comando é invocado, embora o comportamento do comando adicional é influenciado por fatores de comando específico, como o <xref:System.Windows.Input.CanExecuteRoutedEventArgs.CanExecute%2A> valor.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="482a3-104">In general, when the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseGesture> is executed, the command is invoked, although the command behavior is further influenced by command-specific factors such as the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CanExecuteRoutedEventArgs.CanExecute%2A> value.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="482a3-105">Para obter mais informações sobre comandos, consulte [Visão geral de comandos](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/commanding-overview.md).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="482a3-105">For more information on commanding, see the [Commanding Overview](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/commanding-overview.md).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="482a3-106">Ao definir um <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding> na [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xaml](~/includes/tlasharptla-xaml-md.md)], há duas maneiras para especificar o <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseGesture>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="482a3-106">When defining a <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding> in [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xaml](~/includes/tlasharptla-xaml-md.md)], there are two ways to specify the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseGesture>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="482a3-107">O primeiro modo para estabelecer um <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding> na [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] é definir o <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding.Gesture%2A> atributo do <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding> elemento, que permite uma sintaxe especificar ações do mouse e modificadores como uma única cadeia de caracteres; por exemplo, "CTRL + LeftClick".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="482a3-107">The first way to establish a <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding> in [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] is to define the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding.Gesture%2A> attribute of the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding> element, which enables a syntax to specify mouse actions and modifiers as a single string; for example, "CTRL+LeftClick".</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="482a3-108">A segunda maneira é definir o <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding.MouseAction%2A> atributo o <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding> elemento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="482a3-108">The second way is to define the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding.MouseAction%2A> attribute of the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding> element.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="482a3-109">Ambos os modos de configuração de <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseGesture> são equivalentes e modificar o mesmo objeto subjacente, mas haverá um conflito se os dois são usados.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="482a3-109">Both ways of setting the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseGesture> are equivalent and modify the same underlying object, but there will be a conflict if both are used.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="482a3-110">No caso de quando o <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding.MouseAction%2A> e <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding.Gesture%2A> atributos são definidos, o gesto é inválido.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="482a3-110">In the case when the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding.MouseAction%2A> and the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding.Gesture%2A> attributes are both set, the gesture is invalid.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="482a3-111">Em geral, é recomendável que você use somente o <xref:System.Windows.Input.KeyBinding.Gesture%2A> de atributo de [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)], mesmo se você não especificar modificadores; Isso evita a ambiguidade, fornece a sintaxe mais simplificada e fornece a representação mais simples para serialização.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="482a3-111">In general, it is recommended that you use only the <xref:System.Windows.Input.KeyBinding.Gesture%2A> attribute from [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)], even if you do not specify modifiers; this avoids ambiguity, provides the most streamlined syntax, and provides the most straightforward representation for serialization.</span></span>  
  
